ls   = List of files
ls -l /var  = List of file with lenght
ls -a /var  = list of files with hidden files also
df   = display information of file system and file system its usig
man ls = see the all commend user manual
-> then type h
type g for going start of the page
type G for going bottom of the page
/   = for search a string
type n for go down
type N for go up
<commend name> help  = to see the commend details
man -k <commend>  = see the manual commend details
man <commend>  = see the manual commend details
man -k "search string"  = this will search in whole manual to find the sting and details
ostnamectl  = check os information
history   = to see the typed commend hostory
history -d <number of the line> = delete the scpecific commend from history
history -c = delete the entire history
type any commend with an space  = the commend dont save in the history
HISTTIMEFORMAT="%d/%m/%y %T " = to set time and date for commend history


